Description: Floor sherd of East Greek (South Ionian?) pottery cup; buff clay with silver mica; interior reserved with one, worn, glaze ring; underside: part of two rings preserved; inscription cut on underside.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis) (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.857)
